International Business Machines Corp Cuts U.S. Jobs Amid Global Reduction-DJ
Thursday, 13 Jun 2013 08:24am EDT
Dow Jones reported that according to Bloomberg International Business Machines Corp began cutting jobs in the U.S. as part of a global restructuring plan announced in April, 2013. The cuts will affect employees from rank-and-file staff to executives. Some U.S. workers began receiving notifications of the cuts the night before.Â 
